    <string name="settings_navic_title">Location accuracy &amp; NavIC</string>
    <string name="settings_navic_body">gpstools uses your device\'s GNSS hardware for high-accuracy positioning. Most phones sold in India support NavIC (IRNSS), India\'s own satellite navigation system, alongside GPS, GLONASS, Galileo and BeiDou. Using more constellations means a faster, more reliable fix — especially across India. The accuracy shown on the stamp (±N m) is the device\'s own estimate; NavIC support and real-world accuracy depend on your phone and surroundings (open sky is best).</string>
